To style a Lightning Web Component (LWC) without using the `<link>` tag, you can use the following approaches:

1. **Scoped CSS**: Create a CSS file with the same name as your component and place it in the same folder. This CSS file will automatically be applied to your component.

2. **Static Resources**: Upload your CSS files as static resources in Salesforce and then load them dynamically using JavaScript.

3. **Inline Styles**: Apply styles directly to elements using the `style` attribute.

### Approach 1: Scoped CSS

Create a file named `orderForm.css` in the same folder as your [`orderForm.js`](command:_github.copilot.openRelativePath?%5B%7B%22scheme%22%3A%22file%22%2C%22authority%22%3A%22%22%2C%22path%22%3A%22%2FUsers%2Fthbui%2FDocuments%2FSalesforce%2FOMS%2Fforce-app%2Fmain%2Fdefault%2Flwc%2ForderForm%2ForderForm.js%22%2C%22query%22%3A%22%22%2C%22fragment%22%3A%22%22%7D%5D "/Users/thbui/Documents/Salesforce/OMS/force-app/main/default/lwc/orderForm/orderForm.js") and `orderForm.html`. Add your styles to this file.

