To modify the selected code to return the first object in the list if the list exists and its size is not zero, you can update the methods to query for a list and then check the size of the list before returning the first object. Here is the updated code:

```apex
@AuraEnabled
public static Treating_Physician_Information__c getPhysicianFromId(String physicianId) {
    try {
        String searchTerm = '%' + physicianId + '%';
        String query = 'SELECT Name, Id, FirstName__c, LastName__c, Phone__c, Email__c, NPI__c, Ordering_Account__c FROM Treating_Physician_Information__c WHERE Id LIKE :searchTerm';
        List<Treating_Physician_Information__c> results = Database.query(query);
        if (results != null && !results.isEmpty()) {
            return results[0];
        }
        return null;
    } catch (Exception e) {
        throw new AuraHandledException(e.getMessage());
    }
}

@AuraEnabled
public static Ordering_Account__c getFacilityFromId(String facilityId) {
    try {
        String searchTerm = '%' + facilityId + '%';
        String query = 'SELECT Name, Id, FacilityName__c, Address__c, City__c, State__c, ZipCode__c, Country__c, Phone__c, Email__c FROM Ordering_Account__c WHERE Id LIKE :searchTerm';
        List<Ordering_Account__c> results = Database.query(query);
        if (results != null && !results.isEmpty()) {
            return results[0];
        }
        return null;
    } catch (Exception e) {
        throw new AuraHandledException(e.getMessage());
    }
}
```

